The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves combinatorial auctions, which are a type of optimization problem (cs.DS). The paper uses linear programming and approximation algorithms, which are common techniques in algorithms and complexity theory (cs.AI). The paper also deals with valuations and payments, which are concepts in economics and market design (cs.EC). Finally, the paper discusses Bayesian analysis, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT).
